Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
addSpecialRoute(25.10)                                  addSpecialRoute(25.10)

Name
       addSpecialRoute  -  Incrementally adds special route information from a
       file

Syntax
       addSpecialRoute

       [-help]

       <filename>

       Incrementally adds special route information from a file. This includes
       only special route wires, vias, and metal fill. If the specified  file-
       name  is  compressed  (with the .gz extension), the file is read in di-
       rectly. Use this command after you have imported a design.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes the  type  and  default
              information for each addSpecialRoute parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man addSpecialRoute.

       <filename>
              Specifies the name of the file that contains special  route  in-
              formation,  to  be used as input for the design. Only .spr files
              are supported.

Related Information
              * loadSpecialRoute

              * saveSpecialRoute

              * To check how undo and redo works with this wire  editing  com-
                mand, see undo and redo in the Text Command Reference.

              * To review global controls that affect wire editing, see setEd-
                itMode and getEditMode in the Text Command Reference.

              * Power Planning and Routing chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

              * For  more help on editing wires, see the Editing Wires chapter
                of User Guide.

